05/11/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The International Court of Justice in The Hague will debate BiH's genocide lawsuit against Serbia-Montenegro on 27 February, BiH legal representative Sakib Softic said Thursday (4 November). 
Softic added that the president of the court would meet with representatives of the parties in the dispute by the end of this year to specify the duration and schedule of the trial. 
BiH is insisting on a four-week trial, while Belgrade prefers ten weeks. 
(FENA - 04/11/04)
